The paper focuses on the role of computing in autonomous mobile robots, specifically unmanned aerial vehicles. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and simulation, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of benchmarking, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
